    "body": "### Problem\n\nAs compared to `vim` and also as documented in `:help simplify()`, `nvim` won't simplify leading slashes.\n\nNote a special case:\n> On Unix \"//path\" is unchanged, but \"///path\" is simplified to \"/path\" (this follows the Posix standard).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\n:echo simplify('////////this////that')\n////////this/that\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n```\n:echo simplify('////////this////that')\n/this/that\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\n9.1.0764\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n rxvt-unicode 9.31\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nrxvt-unicode-256color\n\n### Installation\n\npacman (neovim 0.10.2-2)",
